# VisionFlow Analyzer

A real-time Android application that captures and analyzes dynamic on-screen data using screen overlay and OCR technology to extract fast-changing values and generate structured insights.

---

## Overview

VisionFlow Analyzer is an Android-based system that runs an overlay on top of other applications, continuously captures screen data, and processes it using OCR (Optical Character Recognition). It is designed to detect patterns in rapidly changing numerical values and store historical data for analysis.

The system focuses on real-time data extraction, processing, and pattern tracking in dynamic environments.

---

## Key Features

* Screen overlay system running on top of active apps
* Continuous screen capture processing
* OCR-based text and number extraction
* Real-time data logging and history tracking
* Pattern detection and analysis engine
* Optimized for fast-changing data streams

---

## Tech Stack

* Java (Android)
* Android Studio
* OCR (Text Recognition)
* Overlay Service (System-level UI)
* Local storage for data logging

---

## How It Works

1. The app runs a floating overlay service
2. Captures screen frames in real-time
3. OCR extracts visible numerical values
4. Data is structured and stored per session
5. Algorithm analyzes changes and patterns over time

---

## Project Structure

* `app/` → Main Android source code
* `services/` → Overlay and background services
* `ocr/` → Text recognition logic
* `data/` → Storage and history tracking
* `utils/` → Helper functions and processing tools

---

## Purpose

This project was built to explore real-time data extraction, computer vision (OCR), and pattern analysis in dynamic mobile environments.

